  ===========================================
  GLOBAL BUTTON STYLING SYSTEM DOCUMENTATION
  ===========================================

  This theme now includes a comprehensive global button styling system that ensures consistency
  across all sections while allowing for section-specific customization when needed.

  OVERVIEW:
  --------
  1. Global button settings in Theme Settings > Button Styling
  2. Master toggle: "Enable Global Button Styling for Sections"
  3. CSS variables automatically defined in layout/theme.liquid
  4. Utility classes in assets/button-styling.css
  5. Reusable snippets for section implementation

  IMPORTANT: The master toggle "Enable Global Button Styling for Sections" controls button colors
  and styling. When ON, sections use global colors and styling. When OFF, sections use custom colors
  but maintain global vertical padding and letter spacing for visual consistency.

  GLOBAL BUTTON SETTINGS:
  ----------------------
  These are defined in config/settings_schema.json under "Button Styling":

  Typography:
  - global_button_padding_y (vertical padding - horizontal padding is fixed at 20px)
  - global_button_font_size
  - global_button_font_weight
  - global_button_letter_spacing
  - global_button_text_transform

  Appearance:
  - global_button_radius (border radius)
  - global_button_background_color
  - global_button_text_color_primary
  - global_button_border_color
  - global_button_border_width

  Hover Effects:
  - global_button_hover_bg_color
  - global_button_hover_text_color
  - global_button_hover_brightness

  System Control:
  - enable_global_button_styling (master toggle for global button system)

  Behavior:
  - apply_button_radius_to_all (applies radius to all button-like elements)

  CSS VARIABLES:
  --------------
  These are automatically available throughout the theme:

  --global-button-padding-y
  --global-button-font-size
  --global-button-font-weight
  --global-button-letter-spacing
  --global-button-text-transform
  --global-button-radius
  --global-button-bg-color
  --global-button-text-color
  --global-button-border-color
  --global-button-border-width
  --global-button-hover-bg-color
  --global-button-hover-text-color

  UTILITY CLASSES:
  ---------------
  Use these classes in your HTML:

  .button-global-style
  .use-global-button-styling
  - Applies complete global button styling

  .button-global-typography
  - Applies global spacing and consistency (padding, letter-spacing) but allows custom colors and other styling

  .button-section-override
  - Resets global styles for custom implementation

  .button--primary
  - Primary button using global colors

  .button--secondary
  - Secondary button (outline style with global colors)

  .button--outline
  - Outline button variant

  .button--text
  - Text-only button variant

  AUTOMATIC APPLICATION:
  ---------------------
  These selectors automatically get global styling:
  .button, .btn, button[type="submit"], input[type="submit"],
  .product-form__submit, .cart__checkout-button

  FOR SECTION DEVELOPERS:
  ======================

  METHOD 1 - SIMPLE GLOBAL STYLING:
  ---------------------------------
  Just add the class to your button:
  <button class="button-global-style">My Button</button>

  METHOD 2 - SECTION SETTINGS (RECOMMENDED):
  ------------------------------------------

  Step 1: Add to your section schema (before closing schema array):
  ```liquid
  {% render 'button-settings', prefix: 'cta' %}
  ```

  Step 2: Add CSS to your section:
  ```liquid
  {% render 'button-styles',
    section: section,
    prefix: 'cta',
    selector: '.my-section .cta-button'
  %}
  ```

  Step 3: Use in your section HTML:
  ```liquid
  <button class="cta-button">
    {{ section.settings.button_text }}
  </button>
  ```

  This gives merchants the option to:
  - Use complete global button styling including colors (when both global setting and section setting are enabled)
  - Use custom colors but maintain global spacing consistency (when either setting is disabled)

  MIGRATION GUIDE:
  ===============

  To convert existing sections to use this system:

  1. FIND: Inline button styles or hardcoded CSS
     REPLACE: Use global variables or utility classes

  2. FIND: Section-specific button color settings
     ADD: {% render 'button-settings', prefix: 'section_name' %}
     ADD: {% render 'button-styles', section: section, prefix: 'section_name' %}

  3. FIND: Inconsistent button styling across sections
     REPLACE: Use .button-global-style class or the snippet system

  EXAMPLES:
  ========

  Hero Section Button:
  ```liquid
  <a href="{{ section.settings.button_link }}" class="button-global-style">
    {{ section.settings.button_text }}
  </a>
  ```

  Custom Section with Override Option:
  ```liquid
  <!-- In schema -->
  {% render 'button-settings', prefix: 'hero' %}

  <!-- In section CSS -->
  {% render 'button-styles',
    section: section,
    prefix: 'hero',
    selector: '.hero-section .hero-button'
  %}

  <!-- In section HTML -->
  <button class="hero-button">{{ section.settings.button_text }}</button>
  ```

  Product Form Integration:
  ```liquid
  <!-- Product forms automatically inherit global styling -->
  <button type="submit" name="add" class="product-form__submit">
    Add to Cart
  </button>
  ```

  TESTING:
  =======
  1. Go to Theme Settings > Button Styling
  2. Make sure "Enable Global Button Styling for Sections" is ON
  3. Change global button settings and verify they apply across sections
  4. In sections with override options, test both global and custom styling
  5. Test the master toggle: Turn OFF "Enable Global Button Styling for Sections"
     and verify that sections use custom colors but keep global spacing consistency
  6. Verify hover states and transitions work correctly
  7. Test on different screen sizes for responsive behavior
